      <hedline>
        <hl1>Appreciating Salonika</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Stephen A Silver letter on Joanna Kakissis's April 8 travel article on visit to Salonika, Greece; photo</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Thank you for Joanna Kakissis' ''Salonika: Greek Youth Remake 'Seattle Of the Balkans' '' (Next Stop, April 8), which noted that Thessaloniki (the Greek name for Salonika) is more than just ''the ignored, unloved and lonesome little sister of Athens.'' But to truly appreciate the unique history of Thessaloniki -- especially its rich Jewish and Muslim history -- one should have in hand Mark Mazower's remarkable book ''Salonica, City of Ghosts.''</p>
        <p>Stephen A. Silver  Walnut Creek, Calif.</p>
      </block>
